verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Sanctify unto me all the firstborn, whatsoever openeth the womb among the children of Israel, both of man and of beast: it is mine.
verses.verse_html: 2Sanctify unto me all the firstborn, whatsoever openeth the womb among the children of Israel, both of man and of beast: it is mine.

verses.text_plain: And Moses said unto the people, Remember this day, in which ye came out from Egypt, out of the house of bondage; for by strength of hand the Lord brought you out from this place: there shall no leavened bread be eaten.
verses.verse_html:
3And Moses said unto the people, Remember this day, in which ye came out from Egypt, out of the house of bondage; for by strength of hand the Lord brought you out from this place: there shall no leavened bread be eaten. ▼
▼ bondage: Heb. servants

verses.text_plain: This day came ye out in the month Abib.
verses.verse_html: 4This day came ye out in the month Abib.

verses.text_plain: And it shall be when the Lord shall bring thee into the land of the Canaanites, and the Hittites, and the Amorites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, which he sware unto thy fathers to give thee, a land flowing with milk and honey, that thou shalt keep this service in this month.
verses.verse_html: 5And it shall be when the Lord shall bring thee into the land of the Canaanites, and the Hittites, and the Amorites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, which he sware unto thy fathers to give thee, a land flowing with milk and honey, that thou shalt keep this service in this month.

tokens.text: And it shall be when the Lord

verses.text_plain: Seven days thou shalt eat unleavened bread, and in the seventh day shall be a feast to the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 6Seven days thou shalt eat unleavened bread, and in the seventh day shall be a feast to the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Unleavened bread shall be eaten seven days; and there shall no leavened bread be seen with thee, neither shall there be leaven seen with thee in all thy quarters.
verses.verse_html: 7Unleavened bread shall be eaten seven days; and there shall no leavened bread be seen with thee, neither shall there be leaven seen with thee in all thy quarters.

tokens.text: and there shall no leavened bread
with thee, neither shall there be leaven
with thee in all thy quarters

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt shew thy son in that day, saying, This is done because of that which the Lord did unto me when I came forth out of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 8And thou shalt shew thy son in that day, saying, This is done because of that which the Lord did unto me when I came forth out of Egypt.

tokens.text: unto me when I came forth

verses.text_plain: And it shall be for a sign unto thee upon thine hand, and for a memorial between thine eyes, that the Lord’s law may be in thy mouth: for with a strong hand hath the Lord brought thee out of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 9And it shall be for a sign unto thee upon thine hand, and for a memorial between thine eyes, that the Lord’s law may be in thy mouth: for with a strong hand hath the Lord brought thee out of Egypt.

tokens.text: And it shall be for a sign

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt therefore keep this ordinance in his season from year to year.
verses.verse_html: 10Thou shalt therefore keep this ordinance in his season from year to year.

verses.text_plain: And it shall be when the Lord shall bring thee into the land of the Canaanites, as he sware unto thee and to thy fathers, and shall give it thee,
verses.verse_html: 11And it shall be when the Lord shall bring thee into the land of the Canaanites, as he sware unto thee and to thy fathers, and shall give it thee,

tokens.text: And it shall be when the Lord
unto thee and to thy fathers

verses.text_plain: That thou shalt set apart unto the Lord all that openeth the matrix, and every firstling that cometh of a beast which thou hast; the males shall be the Lord’s.
verses.verse_html:
12That thou shalt set apart unto the Lord all that openeth the matrix, and every firstling that cometh of a beast which thou hast; the males shall be the Lord’s. ▼
▼ set…: Heb. cause to pass over

footnotes.body_text: ▼ set…: Heb. cause to pass over
footnotes.body_html: ▼ set…: Heb. cause to pass over

verses.text_plain: And every firstling of an ass thou shalt redeem with a lamb; and if thou wilt not redeem it, then thou shalt break his neck: and all the firstborn of man among thy children shalt thou redeem.
verses.verse_html:
13And every firstling of an ass thou shalt redeem with a lamb; and if thou wilt not redeem it, then thou shalt break his neck: and all the firstborn of man among thy children shalt thou redeem. ▼
▼ lamb: or, kid

tokens.text: and if thou wilt not redeem
it, then thou shalt break his neck

verses.text_plain: And it shall be when thy son asketh thee in time to come, saying, What is this? that thou shalt say unto him, By strength of hand the Lord brought us out from Egypt, from the house of bondage:
verses.verse_html:
14And it shall be when thy son asketh thee in time to come, saying, What is this? that thou shalt say unto him, By strength of hand the Lord brought us out from Egypt, from the house of bondage: ▼
▼ in…: Heb. to morrow

tokens.text: And it shall be when thy son

footnotes.body_html: ▼ in…: Heb. to morrow

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, when Pharaoh would hardly let us go, that the Lord slew all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both the firstborn of man, and the firstborn of beast: therefore I sacrifice to the Lord all that openeth the matrix, being males; but all the firstborn of my children I redeem.
verses.verse_html: 15And it came to pass, when Pharaoh would hardly let us go, that the Lord slew all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both the firstborn of man, and the firstborn of beast: therefore I sacrifice to the Lord all that openeth the matrix, being males; but all the firstborn of my children I redeem.

tokens.text: And it came to pass, when Pharaoh

verses.text_plain: And it shall be for a token upon thine hand, and for frontlets between thine eyes: for by strength of hand the Lord brought us forth out of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 16And it shall be for a token upon thine hand, and for frontlets between thine eyes: for by strength of hand the Lord brought us forth out of Egypt.

tokens.text: And it shall be for a token

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, when Pharaoh had let the people go, that God led them not through the way of the land of the Philistines, although that was near; for God said, Lest peradventure the people repent when they see war, and they return to Egypt:
verses.verse_html: 17And it came to pass, when Pharaoh had let the people go, that God led them not through the way of the land of the Philistines, although that was near; for God said, Lest peradventure the people repent when they see war, and they return to Egypt:

tokens.text: And it came to pass, when Pharaoh

verses.text_plain: But God led the people about, through the way of the wilderness of the Red sea: and the children of Israel went up harnessed out of the land of Egypt.
verses.verse_html:
18But God led the people about, through the way of the wilderness of the Red sea: and the children of Israel went up harnessed out of the land of Egypt. ▼
▼ harnessed: or, by five in a rank

footnotes.body_text: ▼ harnessed: or, by five in a rank
footnotes.body_html: ▼ harnessed: or, by five in a rank

verses.text_plain: And Moses took the bones of Joseph with him: for he had straitly sworn the children of Israel, saying, God will surely visit you; and ye shall carry up my bones away hence with you.
verses.verse_html: 19And Moses took the bones of Joseph with him: for he had straitly sworn the children of Israel, saying, God will surely visit you; and ye shall carry up my bones away hence with you.

tokens.text: with him: for he had straitly
you; and ye shall carry up

verses.text_plain: And they took their journey from Succoth, and encamped in Etham, in the edge of the wilderness.
verses.verse_html: 20And they took their journey from Succoth, and encamped in Etham, in the edge of the wilderness.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord went before them by day in a pillar of a cloud, to lead them the way; and by night in a pillar of fire, to give them light; to go by day and night:
verses.verse_html: 21And the Lord went before them by day in a pillar of a cloud, to lead them the way; and by night in a pillar of fire, to give them light; to go by day and night:

verses.text_plain: He took not away the pillar of the cloud by day, nor the pillar of fire by night, from before the people.
verses.verse_html: 22He took not away the pillar of the cloud by day, nor the pillar of fire by night, from before the people.
